  {
    "Id": "614614",
    "ThreadId": "257083",
    "Html": "<p>Hi,</p>\r\n<p>If you are using MEF as your Dependency Injection Container, you could decorate your modules classes with the <strong>InitializationMode attribute</strong>. You don&rsquo;t need to specify PublicKeyToken of your assembly.</p>\r\n<p>You can read more about modularity in <a href=\"http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/gg405479(PandP.40).aspx#sec42\">Chapter 4: Modular Application Development, Specifying On-Demand Loading Using MEF</a> section where this topic is covered.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks,</p>\r\n<p>Miguel Bronzovic<br /><a href=\"http://blogs.southworks.net/mbronzovic\">http://blogs.southworks.net/mbronzovic</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
    "PostedDate": "2011-05-18T06:58:44.923-07:00",
    "UserRole": null,
    "MarkedAsAnswerDate": null
  }
